H0.text: In humans, epicondylitis affects which part of the body. Shoulder

H1.text: In humans, epicondylitis affects which part of the body. Knee

H2.text: In humans, epicondylitis affects which part of the body. Wrist

H3.text: In humans, epicondylitis affects which part of the body. Elbow

A4.text: Epicondyles are on the medial and lateral aspects of the elbow

A5.text: Palpating the medial and lateral epicondyles to assess for pain or tenderness can help determine whether the epicondylitis is medial or lateral
